The key concept here is the frontier: a free cell with at least one unknown neighbour. These frontiers represent\
the boundary between explored and unexplored space, as illustrated in Figure \cf3 2\cf2 . By repeatedly selecting and\
navigating to frontier regions, the robot incrementally reveals the entire map. This paradigm is widely used\
in many real-world exploration applications, including the DARPA Subterranean Challenge
