What is Provided\
You receive a complete simulation framework so that you can focus exclusively on the exploration logic. The\
starter code includes:\
\'95 A 2D environment simulator with three test maps: an open room with pillars, a multi-room office, and\
cave-like passages.\
\'95 A raycasting-based lidar sensor model (360\'b0 field of view, 3 m range).\
\'95 An occupancy grid mapper that maintains free, occupied, and unknown cell states.\
\'95 A Dijkstra-based path planner with obstacle inflation, along with path validation utilities.\
\'95 Live visualization that shows the exploration in real time.\
\'95 A working random baseline: random frontier detection and random goal selection, fully wired into the\
exploration loop. You can run the starter code out of the box and immediately see a robot exploring\'97just\
very inefficiently.\
You do not need to implement any perception, mapping, SLAM, or low-level planning infrastructure. You\
start with a functioning (but inefficient) system and make it intelligent.\

