Part 2b: Custom Strategy (6 points) \'97 Design and implement your own goal selection strategy that\
outperforms the nearest-frontier strategy on at least one of the provided maps. Your strategy should\
consider factors beyond pure distance. Some ideas to explore:\
\'95 Cost-utility: maximize frontier_size/path_cost, preferring large, close frontiers over small, distant ones.\
\'95 Information gain: estimate how much unknown area surrounds each frontier.\
\'95 Dead-end avoidance: penalize frontiers deep in narrow corridors.\
